NURSING
CARE
STUDY
SALLYA
CHILD
WITH
CYSTIC
FIBROSIS
FIBROCYSTIC
DISEASE
IS
A
COMMON
DISEASE
OF
CHILDHOOD
AND
THE
PANCREAS
IS
ABNORMAL
IN
90
OF
THESE
CASES
THERE
IS
FIBROSIS
WITH
ATROPHY
OF
THE
EXOCRINE
PARENCHYMAL
TISSUE
BUT
ISLET
CELL
TISSUE
IS
RARELY
INVOLVED
MUCOUS
GLANDS
THROUGHOUT
THE
BODY
ARE
GROSSLY
DISTENDED
AND
THEY
SECRETE
AN
ABNORMAL
VISCID
MUCUS
SWEAT
GLANDS
APPEAR
NORMAL
BUT
THEY
SECRETE
SWEAT
WITH
AN
ABNORMALLY
HIGH
CONCENTRATION
OF
ELECTROLYTES
A
CHARACTERISTIC
FEATURE
OF
THE
DISEASE
IS
THE
WIDESPREAD
CHRONIC
BRONCHIOLITIS
THIS
IS
DUE
TO
THE
STAPHYLOCOCCUS
AUREUS
WHICH
GROW
BEST
IN
A
SALTRICH
MEDIUM
